    # Happy Birthday Michael!

    I'm not really sure what you want or need these days and I'm a bit tight for cash, so I figured I'd do what I know best and that is to make a website.

    I'd like to share a few pieces of advice that I wish I had known when I was first starting college and I'd also like to share with you some things that have inspired me along the way.

    ## Create your own happiness

    Create your own happiness. Do not rely on other people to make you happy. They will inevitably let you down at one point or another, just as you have let countless people down in your own life.

    Find something that you can do by yourself that is empowering and productive. That way, even at the darkest moments in your life you have something to fall back on. Something you can do that no one can take away from you or stop you from doing.

    For me, that's programming. I have found that the best way to pull myself out of a slump is to build something. It's relaxing and it forces my mind to focus on something else. I can do it anywhere, at any hour, with or without anyone else.

    Mia is empowered by her art. She can do it anywhere, at any hour, with or without anyone else.

